    }
  </style>

  <div class="header">
    <div class="header-content">
      <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
      <h1>Lockheed Martin (LMT)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of Lockheed Martin. Math over feelings. One final number.</p>
      <p class="date">Updated March 18, 2026</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    {hasData ? (
      <>
        <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
        <div class="verdict-card">
          <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
          <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
          <div class="verdict-vs">vs. market price of ${currentPrice.toFixed(2)} ({marginOfSafety}%)</div>
          <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
            {verdictText}
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
        <div class="stats-row">
          <div class="stat-card">
            <div class="stat-value">${(latestRevenue / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
            <div class="stat-label">Latest Revenue</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <div class="stat-value">${(latestFCF / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
            <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <div class="stat-value">${latestEPS.toFixed(2)}</div>
            <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <div class="stat-value">{((opIncome[0] / latestRevenue) * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
            <div class="stat-label">Operating Margin</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <div class="stat-value">${(netCashVal / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
            <div class="stat-label">Net Cash</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
        <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
        <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model. No multiples, no comparables, no vibes. Just future cash flows discounted to today.</p>

        <div class="method-step">
          <div class="step-num">1</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h4>Start with actual Free Cash Flow</h4>
            <p>Lockheed Martin generated <strong>${(latestFCF / 1000).toFixed(2)} billion</strong> in free cash flow recently. This is operating cash flow minus capital expenditures.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="method-step">
          <div class="step-num">2</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
            <p>We grow FCF at <strong>{(phase1GrowthRate * 100).toFixed(1)}% per year</strong> for 5 years. This is calculated directly from the historical average of the last 4 periods of FCF.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="method-step">
          <div class="step-num">3</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
            <p>After Year 5, we assume FCF grows at <strong>{(terminalGrowthRate * 100).toFixed(2)}% forever</strong>. This is derived as exactly half of the 10Y Treasury rate ({riskFreeRate * 100}%).</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="method-step">
          <div class="step-num">4</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
            <p>All future cash flows are discounted at <strong>{(wacc * 100).toFixed(1)}%</strong>. We use CAPM (Risk-free + Beta × ERP), deriving ERP mathematically from the inverse of the P/E ratio minus the risk-free rate.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="method-step">
          <div class="step-num">5</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h4>Add net cash, divide by shares</h4>
            <p>Enterprise Value + Net Cash (${(netCashVal / 1000).toFixed(2)}B) = Equity Value. Divide by shares outstanding ({latestShares}M) for the per-share intrinsic value.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
        <h2>The Three Assumptions That Drive Everything</h2>
        <p>We're making exactly <strong>three</strong> mathematically derived judgment calls.</p>

        <div class="assumption-grid">
          <div class="assumption-card">
            <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
            <div class="value">{(phase1GrowthRate * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
            <div class="rationale">
              Averaged from historical FCF. Growth represents historical trends rather than arbitrary constants. We bound it at 3% floor to reflect stable defense base.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="assumption-card">
